OL,3,CHusband: 'I didn't help my wife
OL,4,Cbecause she intended to end her life'
OL,6,F"She said she had had enough," said
OL,7,FMorgan of that period. "She always
OL,8,Fmade it clear that if things got too
OL,9,Fmuch for her, she would end things in
OL,10,Fher own way. And I got the impression
OL,11,Fthat it had got to that point. That
OL,12,Fthat was exactly what she wanted to
OL,13,Fdo."
OL,15,F"What had got too much?" asked his
OL,16,Fbarrister, Richard English.
OL,18,F"I don't know, she never said. She
OL,19,Fwouldn't explain it."
