OL,3,CHusband: 'I didn't help my wife
OL,4,Cbecause she intended to end her life'
OL,6,FSecurity manager Morgan spoke of
OL,7,Fworking long hours in south Cumbria
OL,8,Fbut that he would ask her daily if
OL,9,Fthere was anything she wanted. He
OL,10,Fnoted his wife was latterly "frail,
OL,11,Funderweight, lethargic" and recalled
OL,12,Fher saying she "couldn't be bothered"
OL,13,Fwashing herself.
OL,15,FIn mid-January 2021, Morgan said she
OL,16,Fmoved from their first-floor bedroom
OL,17,Fto a downstairs living room, where she
OL,18,Flay on a sofa bundled up in blankets.
OL,19,FMorgan said he hadn't noticed that the
OL,20,Fsofa "stank of urine", as a police
OL,21,Fofficer would later observe.
