OL,3,CHusband: 'I didn't help my wife
OL,4,Cbecause she intended to end her life'
OL,6,F"I wouldn't have gone against her
OL,7,Fwishes regardless of what I might
OL,8,Fwant. It's what she wanted."
OL,10,FMr English asked: "Why not go against
OL,11,Fher wishes?"
OL,13,FMorgan said: "Because it's her wishes.
OL,14,FThat's what she wanted."
OL,16,FAsked how he felt when Mrs Morgan
OL,17,Fdied, he replied: "Terrible. I had
OL,18,Fjust lost the best part of 30 years of
OL,19,Fmy life."
OL,21,FThe trial continues.
